description:
The Angolan government announced that as of January 31, 2022, the borders of the Republic of Angola remain closed, except for the following situations,
which are subject to a health control regime:
(i) Return to national territory by nationals and foreign residents;
(ii) Return of foreign citizens holders of work visas and citizens holding a refugee
card;
(iii) Entry of citizens holding an investor's visa;
(iv) Entry of citizens holding a temporary stay visa;
(v) Return of foreign citizens to the respective countries of origin;
(vi) Official travel or business trips;
(vii) Entry and exit of cargo, goods, and postal packages;
(viii) Humanitarian aid;
(ix) Medical emergencies;
(x) Technical stopovers;
(xi) Entry and exit of diplomatic and consular personnel; and
(xii) Transfer of mortal remains, provided the cause of death was not infection by
Covid-19.
